<subSubSection id="C317ABC4D9677A37FF2CFB0FFE1CDB62" pageId="22" pageNumber="545" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB2F84FD9677A37FF2CFB0FFE1CDB62" blockId="22.[151,1437,1197,1403]" pageId="22" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis id="B979245DD9677A37FF2CFB0FFED9DB09" bold="true" box="[199,322,1269,1296]" pageId="22" pageNumber="545">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body flattened dorso-ventrally; elytra without centrobasal crest or carina; sides of the prothorax divergent from anterior margin to lateral antebasal spines; mesotibiae sulcate in apical third; femora and tibiae progressively elongated; profemur more robust; mesofemur subclavate and metafemur more linear. Number of species currently included: 4.
</paragraph>
